\newlabel{tab:unified_2024_big}{{I}{3}{Unified Qualitative Benchmark of Frequency Estimators (relay-class, non-synchronized context). Scores: $0$=Fail, $1$=Poor, $2$=Fair, $3$=Excellent. $h_{\mathrm {HU}}$: Harmonic/Unbalance Immunity; $r_{32.5}$: rejection of 32.5\,Hz IBR interharmonic (a converter-switching-characteristic sub-synchronous component used in Scenarios~D--E; see Section~\ref {sec:scenarios}); $n_{\mathrm {sens}}$: noise floor sensitivity; $n_{\mathrm {NG}}$: Non-Gaussian noise robustness; Latency class: P1\,$<$\,20\,ms, P2: 20--40\,ms, M1\,$>$\,40\,ms, P3: sub-cycle ($<$1\,ms); $v_{\mathrm {RT}}$: real-time viability (3=embedded, 0=GPU only); RoCoF Out.: S\,=\,explicit state output, D\,=\,implicit differentiation; \emph {Phase Resp.}: phase-jump settling (D=cycle-slip, S=settles); $^\dagger $IpDFT latency\,$=N_c/f_0$: 33\,ms at $N_c\!=\!2$ to 167\,ms at $N_c\!=\!10$}{table.caption.1}{}}
